This is Perl module Class::Sasya.

DESCRIPTION

"sasya" is one of the chocolate confectioneries that represent Japan.
It piles a chocolate as thin as the fiber like the layer,
is woven delicately, and is very delicious.

INSTALLATION

Class::Sasya installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is set up,
you should just be able to do

    % cpan Class::Sasya

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

Class::Sasya documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Class::Sasya

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

Satoshi Ohkubo
